## Push Summary — skrptiq-cli (main)

### What shipped
Comprehensive cleanup — all non-execution slash commands now wired to real data:

**Reorganised:**
- `/dials` removed as standalone → merged into `/profile controls` (renamed from "dials" to "quality controls" to match app UI)
- `/status` removed as standalone → merged into `/runs status`

**Newly wired:**
- `/runs status` — shows active (running/paused) executions
- `/workspace set <path>` — changes working directory, updates status bar
- `/config set <key> <value>` — writes settings to DB
- `/mcp tools` — lists MCP tool capabilities from connection config
- `/hub import <slug>` — looks up skrpt on Hub API (download not yet wired)
- `/hub update` — checks each imported skrpt for newer versions on Hub
- `/tag <node> <tag>` — assigns tag to node in DB
- `/untag <node> <tag>` — removes tag from node in DB

**Only execution-dependent items remain:**
- `/run`, `/resume`, `/stop` — need engine runner
- `/mcp connect|disconnect` — need MCP client runtime
- `/providers add` — needs interactive setup flow

